Anniversary Day
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:-A holiday to commemorate the founding of each New Zealand province celebrated locally, celebrating provincial anniversaries; first anniversary Jan 23, 1855 [check Provincial Gazettes & Regs]. Also called anniversary holiday
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: >[nf 1982 Collins Concise Eng. Dict.] [AND formerly, now Aust. Day.]
